{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Use Australian English|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox Australian rules football season | competition = VFA Premiership season | year = 1943 VFA | image = | imagesize = | caption = | teams = | premiers = ''Premiership not contested'' | count = | minor premiers = | mpcount = <!-- Counted only since 1903, when finals were first introduced --> | pre-season name = | pre-season cup = | pscount = | matches = | attendance = | highattend = | leading goal medal = | brownlow medal = | prevseason = [[1942 VFA season|1942]] | nextseason = [[1944 VFA season|1944]] }}
The '''1943 [[Victorian Football Association]] season''' was not played owing to [[World War II]], which was at its peak at the time.
==Abandonment of the season== [[World War II]] commenced in Europe in September 1939, and had spread to the [[Pacific War|Pacific]] in December 1941. The Association had continued with a full program of football in the [[1940 VFA season|1940]] and [[1941 VFA season|1941]] seasons – with the sole exception that [[Sandringham Football Club|Sandringham]] had competed as an amateur club in the latter season<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|title=Association teams – Preston's haul|date=12 April 1941|page=16|author=}}</ref> – but had cancelled the [[1942 VFA season|1942]] season when it became clear that the competition would distract from the [[war effort]].<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|title=Association against football|date=21 April 1942|page=6|author=}}</ref>
By 1943, the state of war had not changed, and the Association decided on 22 February that it would not resume the premiership for the season.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Argus|publication-place=Melbourne, VIC|title=No Association football|date=23 February 1943|page=9|author=}}</ref> The Association premiership would not again be staged until [[1945 VFA season|1945]].
