{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{italic title}} '''''Dolenjski list''''' is a regional [[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] news magazine covering [[Dolenjska]], South Central [[Slovenia]].<ref name="micja">{{cite book|author1=Michael Biggins|author2=Janet Crayne|title=Publishing in Yugoslavia's Successor States|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0g1CIRHeO4YC&pg=PA25|accessdate=25 March 2017|year=2000|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-7890-1046-9|page=25}}</ref> The magazine was started in 1950.<ref name=micja/><ref>{{cite book|title=Central and South-Eastern Europe 2004|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5J_gAU8c9NIC&pg=PA642|accessdate=1 April 2017|year=2003|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-1-85743-186-5|page=642}}</ref> The headquarters is in [[Novo Mesto]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Marko Milosavljević|author2=Igor Vobič|title=Slovenia|url=http://ejc.net/media_landscapes/slovenia|work=European Journalism Centre|accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=Leopoldina Plut-Pregelj|author2=Carole Rogel|title=The A to Z of Slovenia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oMforkIDPrcC&pg=PA367|accessdate=25 March 2017|date=20 May 2010|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-1-4617-3175-7|page=367}}</ref> It is published on a weekly basis and its website was launched in 1996.<ref name=micja/>
In 1997 ''Dolenjski list'' was acquired by Andrej Bartelj, becoming part of the Salomon 2000 company.<ref>{{cite book|title=You Call This a Media Market?|date=2008|publisher=Peace Institute|url=http://mediawatch.mirovni-institut.si/eng/you_call_this_a_media_market.pdf|accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref> Skupina Krater d.d. owns the magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Piano Media Expands Into Slovenia|url=https://www.pianomedia.sk/sk_SK/23/piano-media-expands-into-slovenia|accessdate=25 March 2017|work=Piano Media|date=23 January 2012}}</ref>
