==Events== * [[138]] &ndash; The [[Roman emperor]] [[Hadrian]] adopts [[Antoninus Pius]], effectively making him his successor. * [[493]] &ndash; [[Odoacer]] surrenders [[Ravenna]] after a 3-year [[siege]] and agrees to a mediated peace with [[Theoderic the Great]]. * [[628]] &ndash; [[Khosrow II]], the last great king of the [[Sasanian Empire]], is overthrown by his son [[Kavadh II]]. *[[1336]] &ndash; Four thousand defenders of [[Pilėnai]] commit mass suicide rather than be taken captive by the [[Teutonic Knights]]. *[[1631]] &ndash; [[François de Bassompierre]], a French courtier, is arrested on [[Cardinal Richelieu|Richelieu]]'s orders. *[[1797]] &ndash; Colonel [[William Tate (soldier)|William Tate]] and his force of 1000–1500 soldiers surrender after the [[Battle of Fishguard|Last invasion of Britain]]. *[[1831]] &ndash; [[Battle of Olszynka Grochowska]], part of Polish [[November Uprising]] against Russian Empire. *[[1836]] &ndash; [[Samuel Colt]] is granted a United States [[patent]] for the [[Colt Firearms|Colt revolver]]. *[[1843]] &ndash; [[Lord George Paulet]] occupies the [[Kingdom of Hawaii]] in the name of Great Britain in the [[Paulet Affair (1843)]]. *[[1848]] &ndash; Provisional government in [[French Revolution of 1848|revolutionary]] France, by [[Louis Blanc]]'s motion, guarantees workers' rights. *[[1856]] &ndash; A [[Congress of Paris (1856)|Peace conference]] opens in Paris after the [[Crimean War]]. *[[1866]] &ndash; Miners in [[Calaveras County, California]], discover what is now called the [[Calaveras Skull]] – human remains that supposedly indicated that man, [[mastodon]]s, and [[elephant]]s had co-existed. *[[1870]] &ndash; [[Hiram Rhodes Revels]], a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] from [[Mississippi]], is sworn into the [[United States Senate]], becoming the first [[African American]] ever to sit in the [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]]. *[[1875]] &ndash; [[Guangxu Emperor]] of [[Qing dynasty]] China begins his reign, under [[Empress Dowager Cixi]]'s regency. *[[1901]] &ndash; [[J. P. Morgan]] incorporates the [[U.S. Steel|United States Steel Corporation]]. *[[1912]] &ndash; [[Marie-Adélaïde, Grand Duchess of Luxembourg|Marie-Adélaïde]], the eldest of six daughters of [[Guillaume IV, Grand Duke of Luxembourg|Guillaume IV]], becomes the first reigning [[Grand Duke of Luxembourg|Grand Duchess]] of [[Luxembourg]]. *[[1916]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The Germans capture [[Fort Douaumont]] during the [[Battle of Verdun]]. *[[1918]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: [[Pernau]], [[Reval]], and [[Pskov]] are taken by German forces *[[1919]] &ndash; [[Oregon]] places a one cent per U.S. [[gallon]] [[gasoline tax|tax on gasoline]], becoming the first U.S. state to levy a gasoline tax. *[[1921]] &ndash; [[Tbilisi]], capital of the [[Democratic Republic of Georgia]], is [[Soviet invasion of Georgia|occupied]] by [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Bolshevist Russia]]. *[[1928]] &ndash; [[Charles Jenkins Laboratories]] of Washington, D.C. becomes the first holder of a [[broadcast license]] for television from the [[Federal Radio Commission]]. *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] obtains German citizenship by [[naturalization]], which allows him to run in the 1932 election for [[Reichspräsident]]. *[[1933]] &ndash; The {{USS|Ranger|CV-4|6}} is launched. It is the first US Navy ship to be designed from the start of construction as an [[aircraft carrier]]. *[[1939]] &ndash; The first of 2{{frac|2}} million [[Anderson shelters|Anderson air raid shelters]] appeared in North London. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[February strike]]: In the [[Netherlands in World War II#German occupation|occupied Amsterdam]], a [[general strike]] is declared in response to increasing anti-Jewish measures instituted by the [[Nazism|Nazis]]. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Turkey]] declares war on Germany. *[[1947]] &ndash; The formal [[abolition of Prussia]] is proclaimed by the [[Allied Control Council]]. The Prussian government had already been abolished by the ''[[Preußenschlag]]'' of 1932. *[[1948]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: The [[Communist Party of Czechoslovakia|Communist Party]] [[1948 Czechoslovak coup d'état|takes control]] of government in [[Czechoslovakia]] and the period of the [[Third Czechoslovak Republic|Third Republic]] ends. *[[1951]] &ndash; The first [[Pan American Games]] were officially opened in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina by President [[Juan Perón]]. *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Gamal Abdel Nasser]] is made premier of [[Egypt]]. *[[1956]] &ndash; Cold War: In his speech ''[[On the Cult of Personality and Its Consequences]]'', [[Nikita Khrushchev]], leader of the [[Soviet Union]] denounces the [[cult of personality]] of [[Joseph Stalin]]. *[[1964]] &ndash; [[North Korea]]n Prime Minister [[Kim Il-sung]] calls for the removal of [[Feudalism|feudalistic]] land ownership aimed at turning all [[cooperative]] farms into state-run ones. *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: One hundred thirty-five unarmed citizens of Hà My village in [[South Vietnam]]'s [[Quảng Nam Province]] are killed and buried ''en masse'' by [[Republic of Korea Marine Corps|South Korean troops]] in what would come to be known as the [[Hà My massacre]]. *[[1980]] &ndash; The government of [[Suriname]] is [[1980 Surinamese coup d'état|overthrown by a military coup]] led by [[Dési Bouterse]]. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[People Power Revolution]]: President of the Philippines [[Ferdinand Marcos]] flees the nation after 20 years of rule; [[Corazon Aquino]] becomes the [[Philippines]]' first woman president. *[[1987]] &ndash; [[Southern Methodist University]]'s football program is the first college football program to be [[death penalty (NCAA)|banned from competition]] by the NCAA's Committee on Infractions. *[[1991]] &ndash; [[Gulf War]]: An [[Iraq]]i [[scud missile]] hits an American military barracks in [[Dhahran]], [[Saudi Arabia]] killing 28 [[United States Army Reserve|U.S. Army Reservists]] from [[Pennsylvania]]. * 1991 &ndash; Cold War: The [[Warsaw Pact]] is abolished. *[[1992]] &ndash; [[Khojaly massacre]]: About 613 civilians are killed by [[Armenia]]n armed forces during the conflict in the [[Nagorno-Karabakh]] region of [[Azerbaijan]]. *[[1994]] &ndash; [[Mosque of Abraham massacre]]: In the [[Cave of the Patriarchs]] in the [[West Bank]] city of [[Hebron]], [[Baruch Goldstein]] opens fire with an automatic rifle, killing 29 [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] worshippers and injuring 125 more before being subdued and beaten to death by survivors. *[[1997]] &ndash; [[Yi Han-yong]], a North Korean defector, was murdered by unidentified assailants in [[Bundang]], South Korea. *[[2009]] &ndash; Members of the Bangladesh Rifles [[Bangladesh Rifles revolt|mutiny]] at their headquarters in Pilkhana, [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh, resulting in 74 deaths, including more than 50 army officials. * 2009 &ndash; [[Turkish Airlines Flight 1951]] crashed during landing at the [[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam Schiphol Airport]], Netherlands, primarily due to a faulty [[radio altimeter]], resulting in the death of nine passengers and crew including all three pilots. *[[2015]] &ndash; At least 310 people are killed in [[2015 Afghanistan avalanches|avalanches]] in northeastern [[Afghanistan]]. *[[2016]] &ndash; Three people are killed and fourteen others injured in [[2016 Hesston shooting|a series of shootings in the small Kansas cities of Newton and Hesston]].
