omic historian)|William Ashley]], English historian and academic (d. 1927) *[[1865]] &ndash; [[Andranik]], Armenian general (d. 1927) *[[1866]] &ndash; [[Benedetto Croce]], Italian philosopher and politician (d. 1952) *[[1869]] &ndash; [[Phoebus Levene]], Russian-American biochemist and physician (d. 1940) *[[1873]] &ndash; [[Enrico Caruso]], Italian-American tenor (d. 1921) *[[1877]] &ndash; [[Erich von Hornbostel]], Austrian musicologist and scholar (d. 1935) *[[1881]] &ndash; [[William Z. Foster]], American union leader and politician (d. 1961) * 1881 &ndash; [[Alexei Rykov]], Russian politician, [[List of heads of government of Russia|Premier of Russia]] (d. 1938) *[[1883]] &ndash; [[Princess Alice, Countess of Athlone]] (d. 1981) *[[1885]] &ndash; [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]] (d. 1969) *[[1888]] &ndash; [[John Foster Dulles]], American soldier, lawyer, and politician, 52nd [[United States Secretary of State]] (d. 1959) *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Homer S. Ferguson]], American lawyer, politician, and diplomat, [[United States Ambassador to the Philippines]] (d. 1982) *[[1890]] &ndash; [[Myra Hess]], English pianist and educator (d. 1965) *[[1894]] &ndash; [[Meher Baba]], Indian spiritual master (d. 1969) *[[1897]] &ndash; [[Peter Llewelyn Davies]], English soldier and publisher (d. 1960) *[[1898]] &ndash; [[William Astbury]], physicist and molecular biologist (d. 1961) *[[1900]] &ndash; [[Illa Martin]], German [[dendrologist]], botanist, conservationist, and dentist (d. 1988) * 1900 &ndash; [[Marina Yurlova]], Russian-American child soldier, author, and dancer (d. 1984) *[[1901]] &ndash; [[Vince Gair]], Australian politician, 27th [[Premier of Queensland]] (d. 1980) * 1901 &ndash; [[Zeppo Marx]], American comedian and agent (d. 1979) *[[1903]] &ndash; [[King Clancy]], Canadian ice hockey player, referee, and coach (d. 1986) *[[1905]] &ndash; [[Perry Miller]], American historian, author, and academic (d. 1963) *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Mary Chase (playwright)|Mary Coyle Ch